 Uitehnhage - The South African Police Service in Kamesh, Uitenhage, are investigating a case of attempted murder after a 23-year-old man was shot and wounded in the upper-body at 18:30 on Saturday. "Police were summoned to the scene in Puffin Street, Kamesh, after two armed suspects allegedly shot at the 23-year-old driver as he was travelling in Puffin Street," said police sokesperson, Captain Gerda Swart. "The victim had multiple gunshot wounds in the upperbody and was taken to a hospital for medical treatment.             "The suspects fled allegedly from the scene in an unknown blue vehicle. "The motive for the attempted murder is not known at this stage and the case is being investigated." Acting Uitenhage SAPS Cluster Commander, Brig Ronald Koll, has condemned the shooting incident and has instructed that the perpetrator/s must be brought to book. "Anyone who might be able to assist with any information about the shooting incident, may contact Detective Warrant Officer Andrew Hoffman at SAPS Kamesh 041 988 8718, 10111 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.  Callers may remain anonymous and all information will be treated with the strictest confidentiality." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 